  "original_title": "\u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0dab\u0dba \u0daf\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca \u0dbb\u0da7\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dcf\u0d9a\u0da0\u0dca\u0da1\u0dcf \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0d91\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Come to discuss the countries that have given loans to Sri Lanka",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Shunichi Suzuki, Minister of Finance of Japan, said that all lender countries are requested to meet at one table to discuss the loans given to Sri Lanka.",
        "Mr. Suzuki pointed out that it is very important to find a solution to the economic crisis in Sri Lanka.",
        "Japanese Finance Minister Mr. Shunichi Suzuki said that Japan will coordinate with Sri Lanka's creditors to find a solution to the ongoing economic crisis.",
        "Mr. Suzuki said that Japan is concerned about the severe economic and social situation in Sri Lanka.",
        "Mr. Suzuki pointed out that Sri Lanka should speed up the negotiations to obtain a loan from the International Monetary Fund and countries that have given bilateral loans to Sri Lanka including China and India should gather at one table to discuss the loan issue."
      ],
